Check if you are washing your hands well
We all know that you need to wash them (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you need to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds for washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
Most of us wash them shorter!
All you need is warm water and ordinary soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
Washing, rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hand, but also: the tips of the fingers (connected or individually) – rub them with circular movements against the inside of the other hand, the spaces between the fingers (intertwine your hands, rubbing your fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb we embrace with the other hand and in such an embrace we turn it moment to the right and left.
In an emergency (when you can not wash your hands) we should wipe our hands with a wet handkerchief, and then use an antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 zł).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the door handles or doors with your hands washed (recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it through a paper towel.
Iran's president says he has rejected a proposal to talk to the U.S., Donald Trump denies it
Tehran did not hold talks with the U.S. side during the U.N. General Assembly in New York, despite the American offer to lift sanctions, Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked for the restrictions to be lifted, which he did not agree to.
According to Iranian President Hassan Rouhani, the U.S. has proposed lifting all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for entering into negotiations on a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear program and the ballistic missile construction program.
Rouhani: Iran will not hold talks in an atmosphere of maximum pressure
The Iranian president said he had refused to take up those talks because of the "toxic atmosphere."
He declared that he had met with American diplomats because he succumbed to the urges of France, Germany and Britain.
But he stressed that Iran would not hold talks in an atmosphere of "maximum pressure."
“And even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in 5+1 format, no one can predict what the end result will be,” Rouhani said.
A day earlier, the Iranian leader had said he did not rule out talks with the U.S., and that the European sides of the nuclear deal had accused the US sanctions on Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran after the U.S. withdrawal from the nuclear deal "are a prerequisite that does not allow" to establish dialogue.
If we can abolish this prerequisite and if America lifts sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America.
He added that he would not rule out a meeting with U.S. President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a conversation in the past week during the U.N. General Assembly.
Trump: 'Iran asked, I said no'
Donald Trump tweeted that he was the one who rejected the Iranian side's request.
“Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said "no!" the president tweeted.
Tension with atomic agreement in the background
France, Germany and Britain are trying to alleviate tensions between Washington and Tehran to save the 2015 Iran deal, of which it was signatories.
It stipulated that in exchange for the lifting of economic sanctions, Iran would give up its nuclear weapons program and the nuclear sector would put the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) under scrutiny.
Since the U.S. withdrawn from the agreement in May 2015, the other signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
So far, nothing has come of it.
Washington employs the tactics of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran announced that if it does not receive a permit to export the raw material, it will limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
