Belgium: Brussels Airlines cancels 105 flights due to Thomas Cook bankruptcy
Though British travel agency Thomas Cook has collapsed, its Belgian subsidiary Neckermann is functioning.
The company, however, has problems.
According to VRT television, Brussels Airlines has announced that it will cancel 105 flights in October due to the bankruptcy issues of Thomas Cook.
Neckermann also laid off 75 employees.
All trips with the office, which have been booked in Belgium, will be cancelled, but holidaymakers will be able to receive a refund.
The court in Ghent also declared the bankruptcy of three Belgian daughter companies: Thomas Cook Belgium, Thomas Cook Retail and Thomas Cook Financial Services.
Currently ok. 12 thousand. Belgians are abroad on trips bought from Thomas Cook.
Another 40 thousand people were to leave with the office by the end of the year.
