The office was reassuring at the time that the customers who bought the tours in it would go on vacation.
Thomas Cook - the oldest and one of the world's largest travel agencies - declared bankruptcy on the night of Sunday to Monday.
The immediate cause of bankruptcy was the collapse of last-chance talks with creditors and potential investors on Sunday.
The creditors demanded that, in addition to the 900 million pound rescue plan already agreed in August, the company earn an additional 200 million as collateral for the winter period, when travel agencies usually have a lower turnover.
However, the company's problems have been growing for several years, resulting in debt reaching 1.6 billion pounds.
